# Echothink-Patch: 0024-narrow-extension-bridge
# Title: Expose a bundled-extension-only device bridge
# Area: extension-device-bridge
# Depends-On: echothink/0004-bundled-workspace-extension.patch, echothink/0007-device-identity.patch
# Spec-Depends-On: docs/echothink-browser-alpha/t22-define-device-identity-and-dpapi-storage.md, docs/echothink-browser-alpha/t24-implement-narrow-extension-bridge.md
# Browser-Layer-Reason: The browser owns the local device private key and reset boundary. The bundled workspace extension needs only a narrow native API for non-secret status, enrollment material, proof-payload signing, and explicit local reset; backend services still own enrollment binding, authorization, replay protection, and business logic.
# Preferred-Surface-Checked: extension, native-required (a normal MV3 extension API is used, allowlisted to the bundled workspace extension ID, and the native device identity component keeps all private-key and DPAPI handling inside browser code)
# Security-Critical-Areas: none (no network stack, TLS validation, sandbox, renderer internals, downloads, history, bookmarks, password manager, cookies, or DevTools changes)
# Native-Files-Touched: chrome/browser/BUILD.gn, chrome/browser/echothink/device_identity/device_identity_service.h, chrome/browser/echothink/device_identity/device_identity_service.cc, chrome/browser/extensions/api/BUILD.gn, chrome/browser/extensions/api/echothink_device/* (new), chrome/common/extensions/api/_api_features.json, chrome/common/extensions/api/api_sources.gni, chrome/common/extensions/api/echothink_device.idl, chrome/browser/resources/echothink_workspace/background.js
# Rebase-Risk: medium (adds one Chrome extension API schema/implementation and reuses the T23 device identity component through a small GN target)
# Validation: Apply inherited patches and active Echothink predecessors through echothink/0018-side-panel-local-states.patch, then this patch with `patch -p1` against pinned Chromium 148.0.7778.178. Build on Windows and verify that component extension lokdibgfmiemhdoogailbfpdggndpolk can call chrome.echothinkDevice.getDeviceStatus(), requestEnrollmentChallenge(), signProofPayload({payload}), and clearEnrollment(), while an unpacked extension with another ID cannot access the API and direct calls still fail the native caller-ID guard. Confirm returned objects never contain private key bytes, DPAPI blobs, access tokens, or raw unprotected key handles.
#
# Notes:
# - The API feature is allowlisted to the SHA1 hashed extension ID for the
#   bundled workspace extension and disables generic component-extension auto
#   grant. The native implementation also checks the exact extension ID before
#   touching device identity state.
# - Public API results contain only non-secret metadata, public JWK registration
#   material, reset status, or a DER ECDSA-SHA256 signature encoded as base64url.
#   The private key and DPAPI envelope remain inside browser-owned native code.
# - signProofPayload is intentionally limited to the bundled extension. T25/T26
#   still own the canonical request-proof payload and Echothink-domain allowlist
#   for protected API requests; T24 only provides the narrow bridge boundary.
# - The extension manifest is unchanged: no broad host permissions, native
#   messaging, management, cookies, webRequest, downloads, history, bookmarks,
#   debugger, or DevTools permissions are added.

